### Hello World with Dexie.js (Vanilla JavaScript, ES Modules)

Source: https://github.com/dexie/dexie.js/blob/master/README.md

This snippet demonstrates a basic 'Hello World' example using Dexie.js in vanilla JavaScript with ES module imports. It initializes a database, defines a store, adds a record, and queries for data, showcasing asynchronous operations with `await`.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n  <head>\n    <script type=\"module\">\n      // Import Dexie\n      import { Dexie } from 'https://unpkg.com/dexie/dist/modern/dexie.mjs';\n\n      //\n      // Declare Database\n      //\n      const db = new Dexie('FriendDatabase');\n      db.version(1).stores({\n        friends: '++id, age'\n      });\n\n      //\n      // Play with it\n      //\n      try {\n        await db.friends.add({ name: 'Alice', age: 21 });\n\n        const youngFriends = await db.friends\n            .where('age')\n            .below(30)\n            .toArray();\n\n        alert(`My young friends: ${JSON.stringify(youngFriends)}`);\n      } catch (e) {\n        alert(`Oops: ${e}`);\n      }\n    </script>\n  </head>\n</html>
```

