### Hello World with Dexie.js (Vanilla JavaScript, Legacy Script Tags)

Source: https://github.com/dexie/dexie.js/blob/master/README.md

This example shows a 'Hello World' implementation using Dexie.js in vanilla JavaScript, loaded via a traditional script tag. It covers database declaration, adding data, and querying, using `.then()` for asynchronous flow.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n  <head>\n    <script src=\"https://unpkg.com/dexie/dist/dexie.js\"></script>\n    <script>\n\n      //\n      // Declare Database\n      //\n      const db = new Dexie('FriendDatabase');\n      db.version(1).stores({\n        friends: '++id, age'\n      });\n\n      //\n      // Play with it\n      //\n      db.friends.add({ name: 'Alice', age: 21 }).then(() => {\n        return db.friends\n          .where('age')\n          .below(30)\n          .toArray();\n      }).then(youngFriends => {\n        alert (`My young friends: ${JSON.stringify(youngFriends)}`);\n      }).catch (e => {\n        alert(`Oops: ${e}`);\n      });\n\n    </script>\n  </head>\n</html>
```

